# [Project Name] — Claude Code Session Instructions

## Read before doing anything else — mandatory, in this order
1. Read KNOWLEDGE_REGISTRY.md in this directory
2. Read PROJECT_CONTEXT.md in this directory
3. Read METHODOLOGY.md in this directory
4. Read [DOMAIN]_ARCH.md for each active domain in this session
   (check KNOWLEDGE_REGISTRY.md Domain Registry for the list)

## Workspace layout
  [repo-name-1]/     [description — e.g. upstream BSP layer, read-only reference]
  [repo-name-2]/     [description — e.g. custom BSP layer, files to be modified]
  [repo-name-3]/     [description — e.g. build config repo]
  [local-file.yml]   [description — e.g. local kas config, gitignored]
  [build/]           [description — DO NOT TOUCH — build output]
  [prebuilts/]       [description — DO NOT TOUCH — vendor binaries, never commit]
  [scripts/]         [description — ignore — prior session artifacts]

## Standing constraints — project-specific
- [Project constraint 1 — e.g. "M3 image is working — zero regression on all changes"]
- [Project constraint 2 — e.g. "Never replace cdt.bin"]
- [Project constraint 3 — e.g. "Never mix xbl_s.melf and xbl_config.elf across packages"]
- Never commit any binary to any git repository
- Never run [build system] unless explicitly instructed

## Standing constraints — always apply (from METHODOLOGY.md)
- Read upstream files before generating any replacement (domain F1 principle)
- Apply Gap Analysis Evidence Protocol — tag all findings VERIFIED/INFERRED/ASSUMED
- If a design decision arises not covered by the session spec, STOP and report
- Apply domain checklist (F3) before generating any file
- Show proposed change and wait for approval before applying — one fix at a time
